00:01:11.776 --> 00:01:13.886
The first thing I
want to talk about is

00:01:13.886 --> 00:01:15.216
where iAd Producer came from.

00:01:15.816 --> 00:01:18.476
And I think some of you,
especially those of you here

00:01:18.476 --> 00:01:21.626
that want to hear about iBooks,
are probably asking yourselves,

00:01:21.626 --> 00:01:24.476
"Why am I going to talk about
this thing called iAd Producer,

00:01:24.846 --> 00:01:27.016
what do iAds have
to do with iBooks?"

00:01:27.316 --> 00:01:28.096
It's a really good question.

00:01:28.426 --> 00:01:32.236
And to answer that question,
we'll go back to 2010

00:01:32.236 --> 00:01:33.946
when iAd Producer
was first released.

00:01:34.316 --> 00:01:37.866
Now, iAd Producer was
designed to be a great app

00:01:38.276 --> 00:01:41.336
for creating interactive
rich media ads for iAd.

00:01:41.886 --> 00:01:44.916
And the interesting
thing about these ads is

00:01:44.916 --> 00:01:46.426
that they're actually
implemented

00:01:46.526 --> 00:01:47.606
with web-based tools.

00:01:47.976 --> 00:01:50.626
So under the hood, these
ads are actually bundles

00:01:50.626 --> 00:01:53.376
of HTML, JavaScript, and CSS.

00:01:55.056 --> 00:01:57.066
And so by virtue of
being a really great app

00:01:57.156 --> 00:01:58.856
for creating these ads,

00:01:59.006 --> 00:02:01.866
iAd Producer is actually
a really great app

00:02:02.176 --> 00:02:03.646
for producing content
for WebKit.

00:02:04.146 --> 00:02:07.496
So we've got this
app, it's really great

00:02:07.496 --> 00:02:08.705
at producing content for WebKit.

00:02:09.485 --> 00:02:11.086
And we looked around
Apple and asked,

00:02:11.326 --> 00:02:13.486
"Are there any other platforms
that could really benefit

00:02:13.776 --> 00:02:15.646
from having this
kind of an app?"

00:02:15.786 --> 00:02:17.316
And it turns out,
the answer is yes.

00:02:17.926 --> 00:02:22.986
So iBooks Author has a feature
that allows you to embed custom,

00:02:22.986 --> 00:02:24.706
interactive widgets
into your books

00:02:25.286 --> 00:02:27.696
and those widgets are
built with web-based tools

00:02:28.156 --> 00:02:29.886
and they run inside WebKit.

00:02:30.916 --> 00:02:33.976
You also might be familiar
with iTunes LP and Extras.

00:02:34.326 --> 00:02:37.676
These are interactive album
liner notes and movie extras

00:02:37.866 --> 00:02:38.566
and they're great way

00:02:38.566 --> 00:02:40.466
to experience your
music and movies.

00:02:40.866 --> 00:02:42.446
They're built with
web-based tools

00:02:42.666 --> 00:02:44.626
and they also run inside WebKit.

00:02:45.316 --> 00:02:47.776
So we realized that if we
could take iAd Producer

00:02:48.036 --> 00:02:50.976
and tweak it just a little
bit, we could have one app

00:02:50.976 --> 00:02:53.646
that can produce content for
all three of these platforms.

00:02:54.486 --> 00:02:56.186
And with our latest
release of iAd Producer,

00:02:56.476 --> 00:02:59.136
that's exactly what we did.

00:02:59.356 --> 00:03:00.806
So now, we can use iAd Producer

00:03:00.806 --> 00:03:03.356
to create these really great
interactive widgets for iBooks.

00:03:03.866 --> 00:03:05.526
You can see in the
screenshot here on the left,

00:03:05.526 --> 00:03:09.306
I've got a widget that I'm
working on iAd Producer and then

00:03:09.306 --> 00:03:11.196
on the right, I'm
embedding that widget

00:03:11.296 --> 00:03:12.936
into my book using
iBooks Author.

00:03:13.486 --> 00:03:17.396
I can create iTunes
LP and Extras.

00:03:17.396 --> 00:03:19.696
You can see here in the
screenshot on the left,

00:03:19.696 --> 00:03:21.696
I'm developing an
Extra in iAd producer

00:03:21.696 --> 00:03:24.146
and then I'm running the
Extra in iTunes on the right.

00:03:24.146 --> 00:03:29.226
And of course, you can
create ads for iAd.

00:03:29.226 --> 00:03:32.086
You can see here, I'm designing
a banner in iAd Producer there

00:03:32.086 --> 00:03:33.686
on the left, and
then on the right,

00:03:33.686 --> 00:03:35.986
that banner is actually
appearing on iOS device.

00:03:36.496 --> 00:03:39.226
So we've got one app
that can produce content

00:03:39.386 --> 00:03:40.586
for all three of
these platforms.

00:03:40.826 --> 00:03:43.146
Yeah, thanks, yeah.

00:03:43.146 --> 00:03:44.726
Let's get some applause.

00:03:44.726 --> 00:03:45.586
It's pretty cool,
right[applause]?

00:03:47.476 --> 00:03:47.846
Thank you.

00:03:48.936 --> 00:03:51.826
OK, so that's the back
story behind iAd Producer.

00:03:53.006 --> 00:03:54.876
Now, I'd like to give you a
quick tour of the features

00:03:55.006 --> 00:03:58.986
so that you get an idea of, you
know, what's all in this app.

00:04:00.716 --> 00:04:02.556
So when you first
launch iAd Producer,

00:04:02.966 --> 00:04:05.366
you'll see our project
picker and this is

00:04:05.366 --> 00:04:07.336
where you can choose what
kind of project you're going

00:04:07.336 --> 00:04:08.936
to be working on
and you can choose

00:04:08.936 --> 00:04:10.606
from one of our templates.

00:04:10.686 --> 00:04:12.786
You can see at the top of the
window, I've got this tab bar

00:04:12.786 --> 00:04:15.026
and that's where I choose
what kind of project I want

00:04:15.026 --> 00:04:17.706
to create, whether I want
to create something for iAd,

00:04:17.976 --> 00:04:21.266
iTunes LP, iTunes Extras,
or iBooks Author Widgets.

00:04:21.935 --> 00:04:25.226
And below that, you can
see some of our templates.

00:04:26.216 --> 00:04:28.586
Our templates are starter
projects that have a little bit

00:04:28.586 --> 00:04:29.796
of structure already in them

00:04:29.976 --> 00:04:32.186
so that your project will really
get off on the right foot.

00:04:32.856 --> 00:04:34.986
We've got templates for
iAd like you can see here.

00:04:34.986 --> 00:04:39.456
Here are some of our templates
for iTunes LPs, some templates

00:04:39.456 --> 00:04:46.006
for Extras, and some
templates for our widgets.

00:04:46.006 --> 00:04:47.936
When you go to create your
content in iAd Producer,

00:04:48.916 --> 00:04:50.576
you'll turn to the Object
Library to find a lot

00:04:50.576 --> 00:04:53.026
of really great prebuilt
views and controls

00:04:53.026 --> 00:04:54.906
that you can bring
right into your project,

00:04:55.126 --> 00:05:00.106
and we'll talk a lot more
about this in just a minute.

00:05:00.196 --> 00:05:01.996
Also, while you're creating your
project, you're going to bring

00:05:01.996 --> 00:05:02.996
in a lot of your own images

00:05:02.996 --> 00:05:05.376
and your own video
files and audio files.

00:05:05.766 --> 00:05:08.056
And to import and manage
all those resources,

00:05:08.246 --> 00:05:09.326
you'll use the Asset Library.

00:05:09.826 --> 00:05:14.266
As you get more objects
on your page,

00:05:14.656 --> 00:05:16.336
the Layer List can be
a really helpful tool

00:05:16.336 --> 00:05:17.606
to help manage all of that.

00:05:18.126 --> 00:05:20.306
You can quickly navigate to
the object you're looking for

00:05:20.546 --> 00:05:22.466
and you can rearrange how
they're stacked visually

00:05:22.466 --> 00:05:23.106
on the page.

00:05:23.546 --> 00:05:25.036
This is a lot like the
layer list you might find

00:05:25.036 --> 00:05:26.466
in an image editor
like Photoshop.

00:05:26.466 --> 00:05:31.826
When you add custom
interactivity to your project,

00:05:32.116 --> 00:05:34.716
the Action List is where
you can find all the actions

00:05:34.716 --> 00:05:36.646
that are applicable to the
currently selected object.

00:05:37.096 --> 00:05:41.256
And then to customize the
objects you already have

00:05:41.256 --> 00:05:44.276
on your page, the Inspectors are
where you can adjust all kinds

00:05:44.276 --> 00:05:46.176
of things like giving
those objects names.

00:05:46.646 --> 00:05:48.536
You can fine-tune their
position on the page,

00:05:48.746 --> 00:05:51.276
and you could adjust a lot
of their visual properties

00:05:51.276 --> 00:05:52.856
as well along with a
lot of other things.

00:05:53.276 --> 00:06:00.096
And finally, we have a powerful
but easy to use animation system

00:06:00.536 --> 00:06:02.316
and this Action List sidebar is

00:06:02.316 --> 00:06:03.886
where you can control
all of those.

00:06:04.616 --> 00:06:08.036
You can create precisely timed
groups of actions and animations

00:06:08.036 --> 00:06:09.026
and organize all of that here.

00:06:09.026 --> 00:06:13.506
OK, so that's a pretty
brief tour

00:06:13.736 --> 00:06:15.456
of the major features
of iAd Producer.

00:06:15.946 --> 00:06:17.356
Let's dive deeper and talk

00:06:17.356 --> 00:06:20.116
about how you can actually
create the interactive content

00:06:20.116 --> 00:06:23.076
you're looking for without
having to write any custom code.

00:06:23.706 --> 00:06:26.276
And it all starts with objects.

00:06:27.436 --> 00:06:28.546
So this is the Object Library

00:06:28.546 --> 00:06:29.886
that I just showed
you a few minutes ago.

00:06:30.476 --> 00:06:34.216
It's full of a lot of
prebuilt views and controls

00:06:34.216 --> 00:06:37.036
that you can bring into your
project, and they breakdown

00:06:37.036 --> 00:06:38.116
to a couple categories.

00:06:38.586 --> 00:06:40.796
There's a general category.

00:06:41.296 --> 00:06:42.236
This includes all

00:06:42.236 --> 00:06:43.636
of the standard controls
you might expect.

00:06:43.636 --> 00:06:44.576
Those things like buttons

00:06:44.576 --> 00:06:46.616
and image views,
labels, scroll views.

00:06:47.156 --> 00:06:49.716
There's a media category.

00:06:49.846 --> 00:06:52.386
This is where you'll find audio
players and video players.

00:06:52.906 --> 00:06:55.936
If we scroll down a little bit,
we'll see the other categories

00:06:56.446 --> 00:06:57.876
like the multi-cell category.

00:06:58.666 --> 00:07:01.666
This category has objects that
are collections of other views.

00:07:02.026 --> 00:07:05.556
So we've got things like a cover
flow view, we've got a carousel,

00:07:05.766 --> 00:07:07.516
panoramas, image galleries,

00:07:07.516 --> 00:07:08.766
a lot of really cool
stuff in here.

00:07:09.276 --> 00:07:14.516
And finally, there's a dynamic
category and these are objects

00:07:14.546 --> 00:07:16.986
that can be populated
with content at runtime.

00:07:17.336 --> 00:07:20.416
So to give you an example,
there's a drawing object in here

00:07:20.636 --> 00:07:22.876
where when the user is
actually running your project,

00:07:22.876 --> 00:07:24.906
they can use their fingertip to
draw something on the screen.

00:07:25.226 --> 00:07:26.426
It's pretty neat.

00:07:29.476 --> 00:07:31.516
So now that you got your
objects in your page,

00:07:31.516 --> 00:07:33.876
you want to start hooking
some action or some, you know,

00:07:33.876 --> 00:07:35.536
interactivity up
to those objects,

00:07:35.866 --> 00:07:37.896
and that will start with events.

00:07:38.586 --> 00:07:39.966
Events are user interaction.

00:07:40.066 --> 00:07:41.806
So an event might
be the user tapping

00:07:41.806 --> 00:07:44.036
on a button or dragging
a slider.

00:07:45.326 --> 00:07:49.246
And by listening for and
responding to these events,

00:07:49.736 --> 00:07:52.066
you can get a lot of the
benefits of custom code

00:07:52.256 --> 00:07:53.916
without actually
having to write any.

00:07:54.806 --> 00:07:57.876
So let me give you a more
concrete example of that.

00:07:57.876 --> 00:07:59.226
You can see in my
screenshot here,

00:07:59.556 --> 00:08:00.646
I've a got a button selected.

00:08:01.796 --> 00:08:04.766
And I've got a zoomed in
screenshot of our Inspector.

00:08:05.266 --> 00:08:07.506
And specifically, we're
looking at the Events Inspector.

00:08:08.456 --> 00:08:10.506
And this part that
says, Activated.

00:08:11.606 --> 00:08:13.326
Activated is the
name of the event

00:08:13.326 --> 00:08:14.316
that we're interested in here.

00:08:14.556 --> 00:08:16.736
Activated is the event that
happens when the user taps on

00:08:16.736 --> 00:08:17.666
or clicks on a button.

00:08:18.576 --> 00:08:20.776
And in this particular
case, I've set it up so

00:08:20.776 --> 00:08:22.506
that when this button
is activated,

00:08:22.506 --> 00:08:25.006
we're going to run
the Go to Page action

00:08:25.046 --> 00:08:27.446
which will take the user to
another page in the project.

00:08:27.446 --> 00:08:30.616
And specifically, we want to go
to a page called Lander Game.

00:08:31.156 --> 00:08:34.346
And so that's how easy it is
to configure a custom action

00:08:34.706 --> 00:08:37.916
to be associated
with this event.

00:08:37.916 --> 00:08:39.576
You're not limited
to just one action.

00:08:39.956 --> 00:08:43.316
If you want, you can also
trigger an entire action list

00:08:43.316 --> 00:08:45.796
so you have multiple
animations or multiple actions.

00:08:46.296 --> 00:08:50.446
And if you wish, you can also
provide some custom JavaScript

00:08:50.446 --> 00:08:52.066
code and when the
event is triggered,

00:08:52.066 --> 00:08:55.936
we'll run that code for you.

00:08:55.936 --> 00:08:58.156
We've got a lot of great actions
that you can choose from.

00:08:58.346 --> 00:09:00.426
I want to highlight some of
the interesting ones for you.

00:09:01.116 --> 00:09:03.046
We already talked about
the action that allows you

00:09:03.046 --> 00:09:05.536
to navigate between different
pages within your project.

00:09:05.976 --> 00:09:10.436
You can also control other
objects that are on the page.

00:09:10.436 --> 00:09:12.396
So this is really great if
you have an image gallery

00:09:12.396 --> 00:09:13.536
and you want to control

00:09:13.536 --> 00:09:15.446
which image is the front
most one in your gallery.

00:09:15.976 --> 00:09:20.116
We can play or pause
audio or video.

00:09:20.636 --> 00:09:26.386
We can open URLs and
we can prompt the user

00:09:26.386 --> 00:09:29.196
to compose content like writing
a tweet or composing an email.

00:09:29.196 --> 00:09:30.686
So there are a lot of
things to choose from.

00:09:30.686 --> 00:09:36.306
There's a lot more than what
we talked about just now.

00:09:36.546 --> 00:09:39.426
We also have a powerful but
easy to use animation system.

00:09:39.746 --> 00:09:42.716
So this is how you can create
all those fluid animations

00:09:42.716 --> 00:09:45.316
that your users expect
from iOS and there's a lot

00:09:45.316 --> 00:09:47.066
of different things that
you can animate about all

00:09:47.066 --> 00:09:48.366
of the objects you
have on your page.

00:09:48.806 --> 00:09:55.426
So for example, you can animate
its position, the opacity,

00:09:57.496 --> 00:10:01.136
the rotation, and the scale.

00:10:01.666 --> 00:10:04.786
And those are just a few of
the things you can animate.

00:10:04.786 --> 00:10:07.996
There's a lot more.

00:10:08.396 --> 00:10:11.256
So as you create these
animations or you want

00:10:11.256 --> 00:10:14.346
to have more than one action
that starts as, you know,

00:10:14.676 --> 00:10:17.086
triggered by an event,
you use action lists.

00:10:17.316 --> 00:10:20.936
And these are precisely-timed
groups of actions and animations

00:10:21.236 --> 00:10:23.556
and you can group them together
so that some happen together

00:10:23.556 --> 00:10:24.666
or these happen in sequence.

00:10:25.086 --> 00:10:27.036
You can mix actions
and animations.

00:10:27.106 --> 00:10:28.556
You've got a lot of
really great options here.

00:10:29.986 --> 00:10:30.766
So to give you an example,

00:10:30.766 --> 00:10:33.666
you can see the spaceship
has this complex sequence

00:10:33.666 --> 00:10:36.916
of animations it does.

00:10:37.096 --> 00:10:39.026
One really great use for
these are page builds.

00:10:39.226 --> 00:10:41.306
So the same way that in
this Keynote presentation,

00:10:41.306 --> 00:10:42.876
all of these objects
are animating

00:10:42.876 --> 00:10:44.436
on to the slide as it appears.

00:10:44.706 --> 00:10:46.726
You can do basically the
same thing in iAd Producer.

00:10:46.986 --> 00:10:48.986
So you can have animations
that happen as soon

00:10:48.986 --> 00:10:50.126
as the user visits the page.

00:10:50.636 --> 00:10:54.796
And to give you a demo of how
all these objects, actions,

00:10:54.796 --> 00:10:56.096
and animations come together,

00:10:56.326 --> 00:10:58.036
I'd like to invite Chris
to give you a demo.

